    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals with Subtle Accents -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A thematic, non-linear dashboard structure is used to empower users to explore content based on their immediate interests, rather than following a rigid, linear path. The key sections are: 1) Core Concepts (an interactive analogy), 2) The 'Why' (data-driven business/moral case), 3) Global View (an interactive map for regional context), and 4) Practical Application (scenarios). This design promotes self-directed learning and makes complex information more digestible and engaging, which is crucial for a diverse, global audience with varying levels of prior knowledge and different regional priorities. Navigation is handled by a persistent top bar for seamless access to all sections. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: DEI definitions. Goal: Clarify concepts. Viz/Method: Interactive 'Cake Analogy' diagram (HTML/CSS/JS). Interaction: Hover/click to reveal definitions. Justification: Transforms abstract terms into a memorable, positive-sum visual metaphor, avoiding the problematic 'fence' analogy. Library: Vanilla JS.
        - Report Info: Business case statistics. Goal: Persuade with data. Viz/Method: Interactive Bar Chart. Interaction: Hover tooltips show specific data points. Justification: A dynamic chart is more impactful and easier to interpret than a static table, clearly linking DEI to performance. Library: Chart.js.
        - Report Info: Country-specific DEI analysis. Goal: Compare global contexts. Viz/Method: Clickable world map graphic with a dynamic content display area. Interaction: Clicking a country updates the text and data shown. Justification: Provides an intuitive, visual way to explore and compare complex regional nuances without overwhelming the user. Library: Vanilla JS.
        - Report Info: Hiring scenario. Goal: Apply learning. Viz/Method: Multi-step branching scenario. Interaction: User makes choices that lead to different outcomes. Justification: Active participation in a realistic scenario deepens understanding and retention far more effectively than passive reading. Library: Vanilla JS.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
